      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "A 100k-token context sounds large, but in a 20-tool agent with a detailed system prompt and a 30-turn conversation, the budget fills quickly. Tracking the token breakdown by category prevents silent overflow."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "import anthropic\n\nclient = anthropic.Anthropic()\n\ndef budget_breakdown(\n    system: str,\n    tools: list[dict],\n    messages: list[dict],\n    model: str = \"claude-haiku-4-5-20251001\",\n) -> dict:\n    \"\"\"Return token count for each context category.\"\"\"\n    base = client.messages.count_tokens(\n        model=model, system=system, tools=tools, messages=[]\n    ).input_tokens\n\n    with_messages = client.messages.count_tokens(\n        model=model, system=system, tools=tools, messages=messages\n    ).input_tokens\n\n    return {\n        \"system_and_tools\": base,\n        \"conversation\": with_messages - base,\n        \"total\": with_messages,\n    }\n\n# Example usage\nfrom anthropic.types import TextBlock\nmsgs = [\n    {\"role\": \"user\", \"content\": \"What is the weather in Tokyo?\"},\n    {\"role\": \"assistant\", \"content\": \"Let me check that for you.\"},\n]\nsystem = \"You are a helpful assistant with access to weather tools.\"\ntools = [{\"name\": \"get_weather\", \"description\": \"Get weather.\", \"input_schema\": {\n    \"type\": \"object\", \"properties\": {\"city\": {\"type\": \"string\"}}, \"required\": [\"city\"],\n    \"additionalProperties\": False,\n}}]\nprint(budget_breakdown(system, tools, msgs))\n# {'system_and_tools': 80, 'conversation': 28, 'total': 108}"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "horizontalRule"
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Context Overflow \u2014 What Happens When the Window Fills"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "If the message list exceeds the model's context limit, the API returns a "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "context_length_exceeded",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "code"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " error (Anthropic) or equivalent. The agent must trim the window before retrying. The safest strategy is to drop the oldest messages first."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "import anthropic\n\nclient = anthropic.Anthropic()\nMODEL = \"claude-haiku-4-5-20251001\"\nMAX_INPUT_TOKENS = 8000   # leave headroom for the response\n\ndef trim_to_fit(\n    system: str,\n    tools: list[dict],\n    messages: list[dict],\n) -> list[dict]:\n    \"\"\"Drop the oldest message pairs until the token count fits.\"\"\"\n    while len(messages) > 1:\n        count = client.messages.count_tokens(\n            model=MODEL, system=system, tools=tools, messages=messages\n        ).input_tokens\n        if count <= MAX_INPUT_TOKENS:\n            return messages\n        # Drop the oldest pair (must remove in pairs to keep role alternation valid)\n        messages = messages[2:]\n    return messages[-1:]   # always keep the current user message\n\ndef safe_chat(\n    system: str,\n    tools: list[dict],\n    messages: list[dict],\n) -> anthropic.types.Message:\n    messages = trim_to_fit(system, tools, messages)\n    return client.messages.create(\n        model=MODEL,\n        max_tokens=1024,\n        system=system,\n        tools=tools,\n        messages=messages,\n    )"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Dropping in pairs ("
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "messages[2:]",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "code"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": ") preserves the user/assistant alternation that the API requires. Dropping a single message would leave an orphaned assistant turn or two consecutive user turns, which both cause validation errors."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "horizontalRule"
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Scratchpad \u2014 Using the Assistant Turn as Working Memory"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "The assistant can write intermediate thoughts before producing its final answer. This "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "chain-of-thought scratchpad",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "bold"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " is visible in the context on the next turn, giving the agent a form of working memory within a single session."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "import anthropic\n\nclient = anthropic.Anthropic()\n\nSYSTEM = \"\"\"\nYou are a careful, methodical assistant. When given a complex problem,\nthink step-by-step inside <thinking> tags before giving your final answer.\nYour thinking is for your own use and is not shown to the user.\n\"\"\"\n\nmessages = [\n    {\n        \"role\": \"user\",\n        \"content\": (\n            \"I have a list of 5 products: A=$10, B=$25, C=$15, D=$40, E=$8. \"\n            \"What is the average price, and which products are above average?\"\n        ),\n    }\n]\n\nresponse = client.messages.create(\n    model=\"claude-haiku-4-5-20251001\",\n    max_tokens=512,\n    system=SYSTEM,\n    messages=messages,\n)\nprint(response.content[0].text)\n\n# On the next turn, the assistant's thinking is in the context window\n# so it can reference its prior calculations without re-deriving them\nmessages.append({\"role\": \"assistant\", \"content\": response.content[0].text})\nmessages.append({\"role\": \"user\", \"content\": \"What is the combined cost of the above-average products?\"})\n\nresponse2 = client.messages.create(\n    model=\"claude-haiku-4-5-20251001\",\n    max_tokens=256,\n    system=SYSTEM,\n    messages=messages,\n)\nprint(response2.content[0].text)"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "horizontalRule"
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Short-Term Memory Limits and When to Move Beyond"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Short-term memory is the right default for almost all agents. It becomes a bottleneck when:"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "bulletList",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Sessions are longer than ~50 turns",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "bold"
                      }
                    ]
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": " and the context window fills before the conversation ends."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Users return after a break",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "bold"
                      }
                    ]
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": " and expect the agent to remember previous sessions."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Large documents are referenced",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "bold"
                      }
                    ]
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": " across many turns (50k+ tokens of documents cannot all stay in the window)."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Multiple parallel sessions",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "bold"
                      }
                    ]
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": " share knowledge \u2014 short-term memory is per-session and does not propagate to other sessions."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "When any of these apply, supplement short-term memory with summary memory (to extend a single session beyond the window) or vector-store memory (to persist and retrieve specific facts across sessions). The most common architecture is "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "short-term + long-term",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "bold"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": ": a small window of verbatim recent turns, plus a retrieval layer for older or cross-session context."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "horizontalRule"
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Optimising the System Prompt"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "The system prompt is repeated on every API call and charges input tokens each time. In a long session, a 2,000-token system prompt at 50 turns costs 100,000 input tokens \u2014 just from the system prompt alone. Keeping it concise has compounding savings."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "bulletList",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Remove redundancy",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "bold"
                      }
                    ]
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": ": if the same instruction appears in both the system prompt and a tool description, keep only one."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Defer examples to the first user turn",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "bold"
                      }
                    ]
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": ": few-shot examples can be appended as a "
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "user",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "code"
                      }
                    ]
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "/"
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "assistant",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "code"
                      }
                    ]
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": " pair at the start of the history rather than embedded in the system prompt. They are still in context but can be dropped when the window fills."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Conditionally include sections",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "bold"
                      }
                    ]
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": ": for agents with many modes (research vs. code vs. creative), include only the relevant system prompt section for the current session type."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Use structured headings",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "bold"
                      }
                    ]
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": ": a well-structured system prompt (with "
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "##",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "code"
                      }
                    ]
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": " headings) has been shown to improve instruction following and can be shorter than a prose equivalent."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "# Compact, structured system prompt (250 tokens)\nSYSTEM_COMPACT = \"\"\"\n## Role\nYou are a Python code assistant. You write and debug Python code.\n\n## Behaviour\n- Write code that runs without modification.\n- Explain only what the user asks about; do not over-explain.\n- Ask one clarifying question if requirements are ambiguous.\n\n## Constraints\n- Target Python 3.11+.\n- Prefer stdlib over third-party packages when equivalent.\n\"\"\"\n\n# vs verbose system prompt (600+ tokens) that repeats the same instructions\n# in different words, includes unnecessary context, and embeds examples."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "horizontalRule"
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Prompt Caching \u2014 Making Short-Term Memory Cheaper"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Anthropic supports "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "prompt caching",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "bold"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": ": if the prefix of the prompt (system prompt + stable context) is the same across calls, the cached portion is not re-processed and costs 90% less per input token. For agents with a stable system prompt and a growing conversation, this dramatically reduces cost."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "import anthropic\n\nclient = anthropic.Anthropic()\n\n# Mark the system prompt for caching (stays stable across all turns)\nSYSTEM = [\n    {\n        \"type\": \"text\",\n        \"text\": (\n            \"You are a helpful assistant that answers questions about Python. \"\n            \"Always write runnable code examples. \"\n            \"Prefer standard library solutions.\"\n        ),\n        \"cache_control\": {\"type\": \"ephemeral\"},   # cache this block\n    }\n]\n\n# Large stable context (e.g., codebase, documentation) \u2014 also cache-eligible\n# if it comes before the conversation messages\nSTABLE_DOCS = [\n    {\n        \"type\": \"text\",\n        \"text\": \"# Python stdlib reference\\n...\" * 100,   # 5,000+ tokens\n        \"cache_control\": {\"type\": \"ephemeral\"},\n    }\n]\n\ndef chat_with_cache(messages: list[dict]) -> str:\n    response = client.messages.create(\n        model=\"claude-haiku-4-5-20251001\",\n        max_tokens=1024,\n        system=SYSTEM,   # cached \u2014 only charged once per 5-minute TTL\n        messages=[\n            {\"role\": \"user\", \"content\": STABLE_DOCS},  # also cached\n            {\"role\": \"assistant\", \"content\": \"I have read the documentation.\"},\n            *messages,   # variable part \u2014 charged normally\n        ],\n    )\n    usage = response.usage\n    print(f\"Cache hit: {usage.cache_read_input_tokens} tokens | \"\n          f\"Cache miss: {usage.cache_creation_input_tokens} tokens | \"\n          f\"Uncached: {usage.input_tokens} tokens\")\n    return response.content[0].text\n\nmessages = [{\"role\": \"user\", \"content\": \"How does dict.setdefault work?\"}]\nreply = chat_with_cache(messages)\nprint(reply)"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "The cache TTL is 5 minutes. The first call within a TTL window pays full price to create the cache; subsequent calls within the window read from cache at 10% of the normal input token price. Keeping the stable prefix identical (same bytes) maximises cache hits."
          }
        ]
